Americans have a new "smart weapon"
The U.S. military has sent to Afghanistan a new “smart” weapon, known only under the code name XM-25.
The generals believe that this new automatic rifle will influence the conflict there with the Taliban and "change the game" to their advantage.
The new weapon is like a super precision gun.
Its projectiles are laser-guided with a precision of a few meters.
The special 25mm caliber ammunition developed for this rifle and containing a highly breaking explosive, actually works like small grenades.
Ammunition can be programmed in such a way that it will explode at contact with the target but also at any point of its ballistic trajectory.
