With Thursday’s decision, according to which the plan meets the requirements of the U.S. bankruptcy code, no longer exists any legal obstacle for MGM to float back under the tutelage of Entertainment Spyglass founders Gary Barber and Roger Birnbaum, who will become the CEOs of what will be a lightweight studio.
