Clotilde Reiss Case: The Elysee Exaggerated Syrian Mediation
For more than ten months, from July 2009 to May 2010, the fate of Clotilde Reiss, the young French researcher arrested in Iran for "espionage", has kept public opinion in France, put the diplomacy in alert, and accentuated the deterioration of relations between Paris and Tehran.
All under the eye of American diplomats.
