28 August 2009.
Clotilde Reiss has been released from prison for 12 days but remains trapped in Iran.
The Iranian Majid Kakavand, whose extradition the United States demands for illegal trafficking of sensitive electronic equipment to Iran, is released in Paris, on the decision of a judge.
